The corruption case of Zandile Gumede and 21 others has been postponed to 30 November. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge is covering this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The corruption case of Zandile Gumede and 21 others has been postponed to 30 November. The former eThekwini Mayor appeared for pre-trial proceedings at the High Court in Pietermaritzburg on Monday. The NPA has added charges against former eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede. Gumede and her co-accused will now have to answer to racketeering charges in addition to more than 2,000 corruption-related charges against them. More details on #eNCA #DStv403 #TheMiddayView pic.twitter.com/RjpIqtXOA9  She and her co-accused have been implicated in the R430-million Durban solid-waste tender scandal. READ: Zandile Gumede voluntarily steps aside eThekwini ANC branches have come out in numbers to support her outside court.